message.content:
We start by gathering the relevant data from the balance sheet and income statement.

Step 1. Calculate the Quick Ratio.
Definition: Quick Ratio = (Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits + Interest Receivable + Accounts Receivable) ÷ Total Current Liabilities.

From the balance sheet the End_amount values are:
• Cash on Hand = -206636.07  
• Bank Deposits = 2406.99  
• Interest Receivable = 1225.71  
• Accounts Receivable = 1604015.21  
• Total Current Liabilities = 737762.05  

First, sum the “quick” assets:
 = (-206636.07) + 2406.99 + 1225.71 + 1604015.21  
 = [(-206636.07 + 2406.99) = -204229.08]  
 = (-204229.08 + 1225.71) = -203003.37  
 = (-203003.37 + 1604015.21) = 1401011.84  

Now, Quick Ratio = 1401011.84 / 737762.05 ≈ 1.90

Step 2. Calculate the Net Profit Margin.
Definition: Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100

From the income statement:
• Net Profit = -1352379.63  
• Total Revenue = 5755241.17  

Thus, Net Profit Margin = (-1352379.63 / 5755241.17) × 100 ≈ -23.49%

Hence, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "1.90",
    "Net Profit Margin": "-23.49%"
  }
}
